title.narrative: Output 3.1 Enhanced support for children, adolescent girls and families leading to sustained use of safe drinking water, adoptionof adequate sanitation and good hygiene practices.

description.narrative: Rehabilitation of 991 water sources, including borehole repairs and reprogramming to piped water schemes, by UNICEF resulted in basic water supply services for483,626 people(52.9% females; including 7,371 people with disabilities). Construction of 1,452 self-sponsored household latrines and 765 subsidized latrines for vulnerable households contributed to additional 11,564 rural people (52.6% females) using basic sanitation services and nine villages (45% of target) becoming open defecation free. Institutional WASH services in 457 schools also benefitted 250,988 students (52% female) and contributed to an increased in the proportion of schools with basic water services from 64% (2017) to 67% in 2021. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:11/01/2022
